The paper discusses the development of a deep neural network family for visual temporal representations, specifically for video data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of unsupervised and weakly supervised learning schemes, which are common in the neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the modeling of feedback and lateral connections in the visual cortex, which is related to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the learning of egomotion clues and object tracking, which are relevant to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
